<div class="wrap">
<section class="pressure reveal" id="pressure" style="margin:0 -48px;padding-left:48px;padding-right:48px">
  <div class="pressure-inner">
    <div class="s-head" style="margin-bottom:8px">
      <div class="s-tag" style="color:var(--sage-mid)">PERFORMANCE</div>
      <h2 class="s-title" style="color:#fff">Filtration Without Sacrificing Pressure</h2>
      <p class="s-sub" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,.6)">The #1 concern we hear: "Will this lower my water pressure?" Both models are pressure-optimized — so your shower feels <em>better</em>, not weaker.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pressure-grid" id="pressureGrid">
      <div class="pressure-card">
        <div class="pressure-sub" style="color:var(--sage)">5-STAGE FILTRATION</div>
        <h4>The 2.0 Handheld</h4>
        <p style="font-size:15px;color:rgba(255,255,255,.5);margin-bottom:24px">Flexible hose + 3 spray modes</p>
        <div style="margin-bottom:24px">
          <div class="p-stat"><span>Water Pressure Output</span><b style="color:var(--sage)">1.8 GPM</b></div>
          <div class="p-meter" id="m20"><div class="p-meter-fill p-meter-fill--sage"></div></div>
          <div style="font-size:14px;color:rgba(255,255,255,.35)">vs. 2.0 GPM unfiltered standard</div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-feat"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><circle cx="8" cy="8" r="8" fill="var(--sage)" opacity=".25"/><path d="M5 8l2 2 4-4" stroke="var(--sage)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg><span><strong>3 spray modes</strong> — Rain (gentle), Massage (stimulating), Jet (deep rinse)</span></div>
        <div class="p-feat"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><circle cx="8" cy="8" r="8" fill="var(--sage)" opacity=".25"/><path d="M5 8l2 2 4-4" stroke="var(--sage)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg><span><strong>60″ flexible hose</strong> — direct water exactly where thinning hair needs gentle rinsing</span></div>
        <div class="p-feat"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><circle cx="8" cy="8" r="8" fill="var(--sage)" opacity=".25"/><path d="M5 8l2 2 4-4" stroke="var(--sage)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg><span><strong>Jet mode concentrates flow</strong> — feels like higher pressure for rinsing product from roots</span></div>
        <div class="p-feat"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><circle cx="8" cy="8" r="8" fill="var(--sage)" opacity=".25"/><path d="M5 8l2 2 4-4" stroke="var(--sage)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg><span><strong>Massage mode</strong> — stimulates scalp circulation, supporting hair follicle health</span></div>
        <div class="p-box p-box--sage"><div class="p-box-tag" style="color:var(--sage)">PRESSURE RECOVERY</div><p>Only 10% pressure reduction vs. unfiltered. Most women report it feels <em>the same or better</em> because the spray patterns are optimized.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="pressure-vs"><div class="pressure-vs-line"></div><div class="pressure-vs-circle">VS</div><div class="pressure-vs-line"></div></div>
      <div class="pressure-card">
        <div class="pressure-sub" style="color:var(--gold)">15-STAGE DEEP FILTRATION</div>
        <h4>The 5.0 Stationary</h4>
        <p style="font-size:15px;color:rgba(255,255,255,.5);margin-bottom:24px">Wall-mount fixed head · high-pressure design</p>
        <div style="margin-bottom:24px">
          <div class="p-stat"><span>Water Pressure Output</span><b style="color:var(--gold)">2.0 GPM</b></div>
          <div class="p-meter" id="m50"><div class="p-meter-fill p-meter-fill--gold"></div></div>
          <div style="font-size:14px;color:rgba(255,255,255,.35)">Full-pressure — no noticeable drop from 15 stages</div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-feat"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><circle cx="8" cy="8" r="8" fill="var(--gold)" opacity=".25"/><path d="M5 8l2 2 4-4" stroke="var(--gold)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg><span><strong>High-pressure fixed mount</strong> — wider spray face delivers even, full-coverage flow</span></div>
        <div class="p-feat"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><circle cx="8" cy="8" r="8" fill="var(--gold)" opacity=".25"/><path d="M5 8l2 2 4-4" stroke="var(--gold)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg><span><strong>Larger filter chamber</strong> — 15 stages housed in wider body, less restriction per stage</span></div>
        <div class="p-feat"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><circle cx="8" cy="8" r="8" fill="var(--gold)" opacity=".25"/><path d="M5 8l2 2 4-4" stroke="var(--gold)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg><span><strong>Rainfall pattern</strong> — gentle, even distribution kinder to fragile, thinning hair</span></div>
        <div class="p-feat"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><circle cx="8" cy="8" r="8" fill="var(--gold)" opacity=".25"/><path d="M5 8l2 2 4-4" stroke="var(--gold)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg><span><strong>Vitamin C/E mist</strong> — infused water coats every strand as it falls</span></div>
        <div class="p-box p-box--gold"><div class="p-box-tag" style="color:var(--gold)">PRESSURE ENGINEERED</div><p>The 5.0's wider filter body distributes water across all 15 stages simultaneously. Zero pressure drop perceived by 97% of users.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="pressure-callout"><p><strong>"Will I lose water pressure?"</strong> — The honest answer: the 2.0 has a barely-noticeable 10% reduction. The 5.0 has <strong>zero perceived pressure loss</strong> thanks to its wider parallel-stage design. Both outperform the "dribble" reputation of older shower filters.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>
</div>

